The paper deals with channel estimation in millimeter-wave (mmWave) multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of large antenna arrays and low-complexity algorithms also suggests a focus on mmWave technology (cs.MM) and system design (cs.SY). Finally, the proposed technique involves feedback and control channel design, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI).
